        </caption>
        <graphic xlink:href="mgen-9-908-g004" position="float"/>
      </fig>
      <p>The DataHarmonizer is scalable and can process large datasets quickly. For example, benchmarking tests (MacBook Pro with a four-core CPU and 16 GB of RAM) demonstrated that a dataset of 45 000 records with at least one error engineered into each record took 12 s to validate, and 20 s to export to NML-LIMS format. Automated data entry functionality like the ‘Fill Column’ feature took 6–15 s to process, and the file took 28 s to open.</p>
